
Health, Safety, Quality and Legislation Training

Learner Guide: Electrical Engineering (EASTC)

This training forms part of my Electrical Engineering Apprenticeship Programme at EASTC (Ekurhuleni Artisans Skills Training College). It focuses on workplace safety, health regulations, environmental responsibility, and quality standards within the electrical and engineering industry.

Programme Details
Qualification: Occupational Certificate – Electrician
Module: Health, Safety, Quality and Legislation
NQF Level: 4
Credits: 5
Notional Hours: 50
Associated Occupation: Electrician (671101)

Knowledge and Competencies Gained

Workplace Safety Legislation

Developed a strong understanding of safety regulations within the electrical industry, including compliance with occupational health and safety legislation. Learned the importance of legal responsibility in maintaining a safe working environment.

Occupational Health and Safety (OHS)

Gained knowledge of workplace hazards, safety procedures, and risk prevention strategies. Learned how to identify unsafe conditions and implement corrective actions to reduce workplace risks.

Safety Precautions and Safe Work Practices

Understood safe working procedures when dealing with electrical systems, tools, and equipment. Learned how to follow standard operating procedures to prevent accidents and injuries.

Personal Protective Equipment (PPE)

Learned the correct use of PPE such as gloves, helmets, safety boots, and protective clothing to minimize exposure to hazards.

Safety Symbols and Colour Coding

Developed the ability to interpret safety signs, symbols, and colour codes used in electrical and industrial environments.

Isolation and Lockout Procedures

Gained knowledge of isolating electrical circuits and locking out equipment to ensure safety during maintenance and repair work.

Securing Worksites

Learned how to secure work areas to protect workers, equipment, and the public from hazards.

Protection Devices

Understood the use of protection devices such as fuses and circuit breakers to prevent overloads, short circuits, and electrical damage.

Fire Prevention and Control

Learned the causes of electrical fires and how to prevent and control them using appropriate methods and equipment.

Hazard Identification and Risk Management

Developed skills to identify hazards, assess risks, and apply control measures to maintain a safe workplace.

Environmental Protection

Understood environmental responsibilities, including pollution control and sustainable work practices within engineering environments.

First Aid

Gained basic first aid knowledge to respond to workplace incidents and emergencies.

Incident Reporting

Learned proper procedures for reporting workplace incidents and maintaining safety records.

Emergency and Evacuation Procedures

Developed knowledge of emergency response plans, including evacuation procedures and safety protocols.


Practical Understanding

This training has strengthened my ability to:
Work safely in electrical and engineering environments
Apply legal and safety standards in the workplace
Identify and control risks
Use protective equipment correctly
Respond effectively to emergencies

